-- Chinese Shipbuilding Orders Fall 47% on Slowdown, Xinhua Says
-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 2012-01-02T14:29:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-02/chinese-shipbuilding-orders-fall-47-on-slowdown-xinhua-says.html
Chinese shipbuilding orders fell last
year as global economic growth slowed, Xinhua News Agency
reported today, citing data from the National Development and
Reform Commission.  New orders dropped 47 percent to 33.69 million deadweight
tonnes from January to November, Xinhua said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Adam Haigh in London at 
